  <static seed="1007" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/GraphingQuadratics/IdentifyAxisVertex10.pg">
    <statement><p>Find the axis of symmetry and vertex of the quadratic function.</p>
<p><m>{y}={-0.2\mathopen{}\left(x+1\right)^{2}-4}</m></p>
<p>Axis of symmetry: <fillin characters="13" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
<p>Vertex: <fillin characters="13" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x = -1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(-1,-4\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This quadratic function is given in vertex form. We can easily identify that its axis of symmetry is <m>x=-1</m>, and its vertex is <m>(-1,-4)</m>.</p>
</solution>
